        "description": {
            "value": "<p>Built from the spiked tail of a manticore, a <em>spike launcher</em> is designed to launch large, spear-like projectiles. A <em>spike launcher</em> is a <em>+1 striking</em> weapon. It's a distinct type of martial firearm that deals [[/r 1d8[piercing]]] damage. It has the backstabber, fatal aim d12, and kickback traits with a range increment of 120 feet and reload 2. It uses the critical specialization of the bow weapon group, rather than the firearm critical specialization.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"pf2-icon\">3</span> Interact (evocation, magical)</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong> The <em>spike launcher</em> is loaded</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The <em>spike launcher</em> fires a volley of smaller spikes in a @Template[type:burst|distance:10] centered anywhere within its range. Make a Strike with the <em>spike launcher</em> against each creature in the area. On a success, the spike causes the creature to take a -5-foot status penalty to their Speed. On a critical success, the creature becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Immobilized]{Immobilized} instead. In either case, the creature, or an adjacent creature, can use an Interact action to remove the spike and end the penalty or immobilized condition.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Craft Requirements</strong> The initial raw materials must include the tail of a manticore.</p>"
